We want to use limit switches (connected by CANdi) to zero out our Krakenx60 sensors but were unable to access the CANdi device through any imports within the robot program, so we decided to try to connect them through Phoenix tuner X.

Our limit switch configuration is set to normally open. In the self Test we detect that the S1 input is low when it is not pressed, once it is pressed, the S1 input switches to floating, but the S1 closed state is false, even though we have it set to “ClosedWhenFloating” in Phoenix Tuner. We have applied and flashed configs. When we plot “S1 Closed” it detects when it was pressed but it still doesn’t update the state of “S1 Closed” on the self test. We assume that this is why the zeroing isn’t taking effect in the krakenx60’s motor sensor.
